text: May I speak with Mr. NAMESLOTU?
I am calling about your order.
Do you know when it will be here?
I am more than happy to help.
I just need a few details from you.
OK.  And who is it that I'm speaking with?
"Hmmmm... when I've spoken with Amazon reps in the past, they've always introduced themselves by name."
It's a new policy Amazon has implemented for our safety.
"Okay, back to the few details for account confirmation."
Don't you already have that if you're calling about the shipment?
Why all these new safety and security precautions?
"Due to recent data leaks, Amazon will not compromise customers' privacy."
As long as my heater shows up!
I want to help you with this issue.
My apartment has been kind of cold lately!
Showering in the cold is no fun!
What is the address on file with Amazon?
I crank the temperature up to 80 and keep it there.
That's probably why the heater hasn't shown up yet!
You probably sent it to my billing address.
Please pick it up at your billing address.
They found the address as undeliverable.
I've received packages at that address in the past.
"Sometimes drivers put ""Undeliverable"" to meet time expectations."
"Hey, my wife is on the other line."
What number can I call you back at?
